We are interested in the periodic classical solutions to the
Hamilton's equations of (), since these are the basic
incredients in the Gutzwiller trace formula quantization. We start
by revealing their self-similar scaling properties, in a manner
reminiscent of conventional renormalization group transformations.
For this we consider a periodic solution  to
the Hamilton's equations, with some definite values of the period
 and coupling . We then inquire how to scale this
periodic solution to other periods , possibly with
a redefinition of the coupling . For
this we introduce a change of variables in () which
scales , redefines  and
possibly multiplies the action by some overall constant 
 but leaves the functional form of the integrand in
() otherwise intact. The form of Hamilton's equations
remains then untouched but a periodic orbit 
becomes mapped into a new periodic orbit 
 solving the original equations with the new parameter
values .

